## Group Members:
john livingston
spenser leighton
arram mandel


## Name of Session:
disrupting your perspective: become an (secret) agent of disruption

## Session Description 

The benefits of distruption your thought process, or daily life for higher achievement both professional and personal.

## Session Outcomes

quote

ghandi: “Your beliefs become your thoughts, your thoughts become your words, your words become your actions, your actions become your habits, your habits become your values, your values become your destiny.” — Mahatma Gandhi

yoda: "Fear is the path to the dark side. Fear leads to anger. Anger leads to hate. Hate leads to suffering."

sell the benefit of disrupting your perspective, not pushing a certain perspective



(What will students learn/leave with?): 

## Session Outline 



count attendees as they walk into room, divide them into groups that way immediately!!!

who do you like to watch lose?(10 min)

introduce ourselves(3 min)

have attendees think about a business or other idea that they wanted to try but were uncomfortable with it. everyone will share.(10 min)

show john's harvard clip(3 min)

-what are some takeaways/criticisms you have for the video?

John: How can disrupting an industry have massive benefits?(15 min)

Spenser: go into potential positives of disrupting perspective(15 min)

-exercises for disrupting perspective
     -think about something in daily routine that could benefit from disruption

-show thor clip

Arram: talk about confucian idea of no true self and how true self is limiting.(15 min)
     -Whats something that's not considered 'you' that still seems really cool. Can be anything.

wrap up(10 min)

-How can you implement disruption in your life going forward?
     -name one way you'll challenge yourself to disrupt your life.


(Please include who is facilitating and how much time you are going to spend in each section):

